Abuja- The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, has commended former Governor of Osun State, Chief Bisi Akande, for his contributions to governance and political development in Nigeria. Lawan gave the commendation while felicitating with the All Progressives Congress (APC) Chieftain on the occasion of the latter’s 82nd birthday. The Senate President who joined family, friends and political associates of the first interim National Chairman of the APC in rejoicing with the Septuagenarian, recalled the celebrant’s integrity and other virtues as much needed components in the country’s politics. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “Chief Akande’s integrity, consistency, focus, level-headedness, firmness as a leader and principle-based politics make him an elder statesman to be emulated, especially by those who take or aspire to public offices,” Lawan said. The number three citizen added that Chief Akande’s “achievements as the first governor of Osun in this democratic dispensation and as the leader of the APC in its formative stage shall always remain remarkable and have cemented his position among leaders of consequence in Nigeria.” Fayemi’s Aide After My Life – Lere Olayinka BREAKING: Kano State Government Insist Schools Resumes Tomorrow This is as he prayed for more years of good health for the former governor so that he can continue to contribute to the development of the country.